Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pour the boiling @water{450%ml} into a #jug{} with the @vegetable stock paste{20%g}, stir well and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large ovenproof #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, just cook in a normal saucepan then transfer it to an ovenproof dish before the risotto goes in the oven. When the oil is hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Stir in the @risotto rice{175%g} and cook until the edges are slightly translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Next, pour the stock into the rice then add the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Bring it back to the boil then cover with a #lid{} (or some tightly fitting #foil{}). Pop onto the top shelf of your oven and bake until the rice is cooked and the stock absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, cut the @halloumi{250%g} into three slices per person. Place the halloumi slices in a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

== Lemony Crumb ==

While the risotto is cooking, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Heat the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the crumb in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toast them until golden, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring every minute. Once golden, stir in half the lemon zest and transfer it into a #bowl{}.

== Dressing ==

Pop the frying pan back on medium-heat and add a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry. Once the oil is hot, lay in the halloumi slices. Fry until golden, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side, then remove the pan from the heat. Squeeze the lemon juice into a large bowl. Add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}, and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Whisk together with a #fork{} along with the @wild rocket{40%g}.

== To Serve ==

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from your oven. Carefully take the lid off the pan and add a splash of water to loosen if you need to. Stir in a knob of @?butter{knob} and the remaining lemon zest. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Share out the risotto into your #serving bowls{}, top with the halloumi and finish with a sprinkling of the lemony crumb. Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!